    "Gregory Bentley is chairman of infrastructure engineering software developer Bentley Systems. He was CEO from 2000 to 2024.",
    "He joined the company in 1991 after selling a financial trading company he co-founded with brother Barry for $50 million.",
    "His younger brothers Barry and Keith founded the software company in 1984.",
    "Bentley Systems develops and sells computer-aided design (CAD) software for architects and engineers working on public and industrial infrastructure.",
    "The $1.5 billion (sales) company remains majority owned by the Bentley family."
  ],
  "about": [
